00:16:49.120 --> 00:16:51.339
DELTAC has no effect, shown in red here.

280
00:16:52.819 --> 00:16:56.340
Now, to extend this further, Jie sort of looked at a larger panel

281
00:16:57.080 --> 00:17:00.560
of cell lines. You can see that in AR positive prostate cancer cells,

282
00:17:00.940 --> 00:17:04.840
these have very low nanomolar level IC50 shown with the red

283
00:17:04.921 --> 00:17:07.760
bars here. These are AR positive prostate cancer cells.

284
00:17:07.820 --> 00:17:11.580
When he extended this across a panel of cell lines, most normal cell

285
00:17:11.600 --> 00:17:15.340
lines shown in gray are unaffected or very high

286
00:17:15.401 --> 00:17:19.220
IC50s, and AR negative prostate cancer cell lines shown in light

287
00:17:19.260 --> 00:17:21.980
blue, also quite resistant to the

288
00:17:22.800 --> 00:17:26.540
DELTAC. So this is exquisitely specific to AR

289
00:17:26.600 --> 00:17:29.280
positive prostate cancer cell lines.

290
00:17:31.380 --> 00:17:34.560
Now to sort of look at the activities individually of AR and

291
00:17:34.640 --> 00:17:38.480
p300CBP. Here we're showing that the DELTAC

292
00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:42.580
is a very potent inhibitor of p300CBP activity in terms

293
00:17:42.620 --> 00:17:46.420
of its extinguishing this N-terminal H2B mark

294
00:17:46.980 --> 00:17:47.460
shown here.

295
00:17:48.800 --> 00:17:51.820
Likewise, when we look at androgen receptor, this is gene set enrichment.

296
00:17:52.050 --> 00:17:55.660
Androgen target genes are markedly inhibited, shown here, and then

297
00:17:55.720 --> 00:17:57.820
graphically shown in this matrix plot.

298
00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:02.120
These are AR target genes, and then with nanomolar levels of the

299
00:18:02.140 --> 00:18:04.160
DELTAC, they're essentially markedly

300
00:18:05.140 --> 00:18:05.740
attenuated.

301
00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:11.580
Now to demonstrate that a ternary complex actually exists between

302
00:18:11.620 --> 00:18:15.460
AR, DELTAC, and p300, Jie took advantage

303
00:18:15.520 --> 00:18:18.900
of the proximity ligation assay, essentially taking two different

304
00:18:19.160 --> 00:18:22.800
antibodies. And if a ternary complex forms,

305
00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:27.360
this assay then lights up in terms of fluorescence, in terms of a rolling circle

306
00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:31.000
amplification of fluorescence. And you can see here

307
00:18:31.620 --> 00:18:35.160
endogenous AR and p300 in vehicle-treated cells.

308
00:18:35.480 --> 00:18:36.320
We see

309
00:18:37.420 --> 00:18:40.220
a small amount of foci formation shown here with the red

310
00:18:40.280 --> 00:18:44.120
dots.But when we hit the cells with nanomolar levels of the

311
00:18:44.160 --> 00:18:48.040
DELTAC, then we see this marked increase of these

312
00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:51.520
red foci representing, again, increased induced

313
00:18:51.530 --> 00:18:54.380
proximity in the context of the DELTAC.

314
00:18:55.840 --> 00:18:59.570
To look at this in an orthogonal way, we took advantage of a series of

315
00:18:59.600 --> 00:19:03.120
immunoprecipitation assays where Jia essentially pulled

316
00:19:03.130 --> 00:19:03.860
down

317
00:19:04.900 --> 00:19:07.740
p300 and then western blotted for AR.

318
00:19:07.780 --> 00:19:11.640
You can see that the DELTAC certainly induces this interaction, in

319
00:19:11.680 --> 00:19:14.880
fact, sort of gluing AR and p300 together.

320
00:19:15.600 --> 00:19:19.480
This was also seen by IP mass spec analysis, where essentially when we

321
00:19:19.520 --> 00:19:20.000
pull down

322
00:19:20.840 --> 00:19:23.640
p300, the top hit was AR, shown here.

323
00:19:24.420 --> 00:19:28.300
And when we do this in a reciprocal fashion, when we pull down AR,

324
00:19:28.340 --> 00:19:31.640
we can immunoblot for p300 in the context of the DELTAC.

325
00:19:32.080 --> 00:19:35.940
When we pull down AR and carry out mass spec-based analyses, the

326
00:19:35.980 --> 00:19:38.260
top hits are p300 and CBP.

327
00:19:40.040 --> 00:19:43.920
To look at this at a genome-wide scale, we took advantage of ChIP-seq

328
00:19:44.240 --> 00:19:48.220
assessments. What we observed was that in terms of AR

329
00:19:48.260 --> 00:19:52.080
chromatin immunoprecipitation, these are the top AR binding

330
00:19:52.160 --> 00:19:56.060
sites and enhancer sites. When we hit the cells with,

331
00:19:56.520 --> 00:20:00.440
again, nanomolar levels of the DELTAC, we're seeing increased recruitment of

332
00:20:00.580 --> 00:20:01.680
AR to chromatin.

333
00:20:02.620 --> 00:20:06.340
But perhaps the most surprising aspect was that similarly, we're seeing

334
00:20:06.420 --> 00:20:10.160
increased recruitment of p300 to wherever AR was

335
00:20:11.000 --> 00:20:14.780
in terms of chromatin binding. So it appears that the

336
00:20:14.800 --> 00:20:18.620
DELTAC is really gluing AR and p300 together.

337
00:20:20.440 --> 00:20:24.340
We came up with this particular model

338
00:20:24.380 --> 00:20:26.880
in terms of explaining the effects that we were observing,

339
00:20:27.960 --> 00:20:30.300
this idea around domain alteration chimeras.

340
00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:34.240
So these complexes form an endogenous

341
00:20:34.320 --> 00:20:37.140
complex of p300 and AR.

342
00:20:38.920 --> 00:20:42.700
In the context of the DELTAC, the domain-domain interactions get

343
00:20:42.740 --> 00:20:45.420
reprogrammed, whereby the bromodomain

344
00:20:46.260 --> 00:20:50.100
of p300 then interacts directly with the ligand binding domain

345
00:20:50.199 --> 00:20:53.940
of AR, then creating essentially these

346
00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:57.630
inert neomorphic complexes that

347
00:20:57.660 --> 00:21:00.730
essentially potentially lose activity.

348
00:21:03.140 --> 00:21:06.860
So to examine this in further detail, we looked at the AR-ERG

349
00:21:06.900 --> 00:21:10.380
neo-enhancersome in general. You can see, as I mentioned, AR

350
00:21:11.080 --> 00:21:14.720
