351
00:21:14.740 --> 00:21:18.700
chromatin, while ERG as an oncogenic transcription factor in the context

352
00:21:18.740 --> 00:21:21.690
of VCAP cells is modestly displaced.

353
00:21:22.900 --> 00:21:26.780
p300, as I mentioned earlier, is essentially glued to wherever AR is.

354
00:21:27.480 --> 00:21:30.920
BRD4 is markedly diminished. Pol II is

355
00:21:31.260 --> 00:21:31.680
diminished,

356
00:21:33.160 --> 00:21:36.780
as well as the N-terminal histone marks that I mentioned earlier are completely

357
00:21:36.800 --> 00:21:39.320
extinguished in the context of the DELTAC.

358
00:21:40.480 --> 00:21:44.340
So then this brings us to this idea around the DELTAC really

359
00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:47.380
reprogramming the AR cistrome.

360
00:21:48.320 --> 00:21:50.680
And again, this is AR ChIP-seq analyses.

361
00:21:50.880 --> 00:21:54.400
We looked at the sites that were depleted with the DELTAC, shown here.

362
00:21:55.360 --> 00:21:56.720
And when we look at the sites

363
00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:01.540
where AR is depleted, they're enriched for these oncogenic

364
00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:05.960
FOXA1-AR half sites that are, again, characteristic of

365
00:22:06.040 --> 00:22:09.220
where AR binds in the context of malignancy.

366
00:22:10.700 --> 00:22:13.760
When we look at sites that are enhanced by the

367
00:22:14.740 --> 00:22:18.489
DELTAC shown here in terms of AR, we see an enhancement

368
00:22:18.940 --> 00:22:21.620
of AR binding to palindromic ARE sites.

369
00:22:21.660 --> 00:22:25.630
So this is the sites that AR binds to in terms of controlling differentiation,

370
00:22:25.760 --> 00:22:28.780
proliferation, and other normal effects.

371
00:22:30.380 --> 00:22:33.570
As I mentioned earlier, we're talking about a histone acetyltransferase.

372
00:22:33.710 --> 00:22:37.140
So we then carried out mass spec-based

373
00:22:37.380 --> 00:22:41.360
