376
00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:51.960
sites, are markedly diminished with the DELTAC.

377
00:22:52.980 --> 00:22:56.700
But interestingly, we're getting an increase of acetylation at

378
00:22:56.780 --> 00:23:00.640
novel sites in the context of proteins that are part of this neo-enhancersome

379
00:23:00.720 --> 00:23:04.560
complex, including the N-terminal domain of AR and SRC-2

380
00:23:04.840 --> 00:23:08.800
and SRC-3. So these are neomorphic effects caused by the DELTAC

381
00:23:08.860 --> 00:23:09.260
itself.

382
00:23:10.340 --> 00:23:13.720
So then we have this general model where we basically have the histone

383
00:23:13.740 --> 00:23:17.560
acetyltransferase domain interacting essentially with the

384
00:23:17.660 --> 00:23:21.320
N-terminal H2B histones. In the context of the DELTAC,

385
00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:25.500
this gets repositioned to interact with the N-terminal domain of AR

386
00:23:25.620 --> 00:23:28.940
as well as SRC-3. When we look at components of the

387
00:23:28.960 --> 00:23:32.520
neo-enhancersome in general, FOXA1, BRD4, and ERG,

388
00:23:32.900 --> 00:23:36.420
we see that ERG and BRD4 are displaced while the pioneer

389
00:23:36.480 --> 00:23:38.800
transcription factor FOXA1 remains.

390
00:23:39.220 --> 00:23:42.270
And we see this enrichment of palindromic ARE sites

391
00:23:42.740 --> 00:23:46.600
relative to the chimeric AR half sites that are associated

392
00:23:46.640 --> 00:23:49.960
essentially with malignancy, essentially sites where AR likes to

393
00:23:49.980 --> 00:23:52.240
bind in the context of malignancy.

394
00:23:53.520 --> 00:23:56.320
So what does this look like in preclinical models?

395
00:23:56.360 --> 00:23:59.820
This is again a series of human prostate cancer organoids.

